OUT TUESDAY 
🎧 @ 6AM
📺 @ 6AM

The inaugural Football for Change event in Los Cabos—co-hosted by Hidden Pearls and the ABC Sports Foundation—was nothing short of incredible!

Over several days, we engaged with the local community through service projects, mentorship, and wellness initiatives, proving that sports can be a powerful force for change.

A huge shoutout to the San Francisco 49ers players who answered our call to coach over 200+ youth athletes, including 100+ girls in flag football. Together, we were able to empower the next generation through sports, wellness, and community service.

A heartfelt thank you to our incredible sponsors, partners, and local municipalities for their support—your belief in this mission and generous support made every moment of this event possible.

Sincere thanks also go to the amazing production team @vox.pop.branding and our talented videographer @quintonmcameron for capturing the heart of this initiative so beautifully.

And to the visionary organizers from Hidden Pearls and ABC Sports Foundation—@gkittle, @coachkittle61, @thatgirlashleydanielle, and @avery_urquhart—your leadership, heart, and tireless work brought this event to life. You turned an idea into impact and sparked something far bigger than just a weekend of football—you built a movement.

This is just the beginning. 🏈

Stay tuned for Part 2 - Building Purpose: A Conversation with George and Bruce. 

If you or your organization want to be part of the next Football for Change event, we want to hear from you. Whether you’re a coach, a player, a brand, a volunteer, or a dreamer—reach out at info@abcsports.org and join us in shaping what’s next.
